# gen134 (L16/L19): BRANCHING abduction — enumerating the hypothesis space. When
# several rules conclude the same goal, abduction reports every ALTERNATIVE
# explanation, not just the first. Closes the open edge gen131/132 flagged. The
# alternatives are read from the real rule set (kb_rules_for_head /
# kb_nth_rule_body_preds), each naming only its own missing premises.

# Two independent rules conclude pet: cat -> pet and dog -> pet.
> every cat is a pet
< Learned rule: pet(X) :- cat(X).
> every dog is a pet
< Learned rule: pet(X) :- dog(X).
> is rex a pet?
< No.

# Abduction now offers BOTH ways — the disjunctive hypothesis space.
> what would make rex a pet?
< There's more than one way: either rex is a cat, or rex is a dog — any one would make rex a pet.
> why isn't rex a pet?
< rex is not a pet because every alternative is blocked: cat -> pet needs rex is a cat; dog -> pet needs rex is a dog.

# gen137 stress probe: ten independent alternatives, all blocked.
> every alpha is a signal
< Learned rule: signal(X) :- alpha(X).
> every beta is a signal
< Learned rule: signal(X) :- beta(X).
> every gamma is a signal
< Learned rule: signal(X) :- gamma(X).
> every delta is a signal
< Learned rule: signal(X) :- delta(X).
> every epsilon is a signal
< Learned rule: signal(X) :- epsilon(X).
> every zeta is a signal
< Learned rule: signal(X) :- zeta(X).
> every eta is a signal
< Learned rule: signal(X) :- eta(X).
> every theta is a signal
< Learned rule: signal(X) :- theta(X).
> every iota is a signal
< Learned rule: signal(X) :- iota(X).
> every kappa is a signal
< Learned rule: signal(X) :- kappa(X).
> why isn't zed a signal?
< zed is not a signal because every alternative is blocked: alpha -> signal needs zed is a alpha; beta -> signal needs zed is a beta; gamma -> signal needs zed is a gamma; delta -> signal needs zed is a delta; epsilon -> signal needs zed is a epsilon; zeta -> signal needs zed is a zeta; eta -> signal needs zed is a eta; theta -> signal needs zed is a theta; iota -> signal needs zed is a iota; kappa -> signal needs zed is a kappa.


# Take one branch; the consequence is volunteered (gen103) and the goal holds.
> rex is a cat
< Learned: cat(rex). Now rex is a pet after all.
> is rex a pet?
< Yes.
